content:
Transfer a Messaging Session

Increase your capacity to accept incoming messaging sessions by transferring an existing messaging session. Agents can transfer a messaging session to another qualified agent, queue, or routing flow.

To do this:

* In an active messaging session, click the transfer icon in the lower-left corner of the Conversation component.
* Select a recipient type: Agent, Queue, or Flow.
* Only agents who are online with a Messaging presence status appear in the list. You can see each agent's capacity percentage, including agents at full capacity.
* Select a recipient and click Transfer.
* When the selected agent accepts the transfer, the original agent is removed from the conversation and their tab closes automatically.

Agents can't decline transfers, even if the option to let agents decline work requests is selected in your Omni-Channel presence configuration settings. If an agent is at 100% capacity and a session is transferred to them, the session enters a waiting state in which the original agent is removed. The transfer completes when the recipient agent is available to accept it.

User permissions needed:

* Run Flows
* Messaging for In-App and Web User permission set license AND Messaging for In-App and Web Agent user permission
* Messaging User permission set license AND Messaging Agent user permission
title: Transferring Messaging Sessions
